51class QRectVectorPath : public QVectorPath {
52public:
53 inline void set(const QRect &r) {
54 qreal left = r.x();
55 qreal right = r.x() + r.width();
56 qreal top = r.y();
57 qreal bottom = r.y() + r.height();
58 pts[0] = left;
59 pts[1] = top;
60 pts[2] = right;
61 pts[3] = top;
62 pts[4] = right;
63 pts[5] = bottom;
64 pts[6] = left;
65 pts[7] = bottom;
66 }
67
68 inline void set(const QRectF &r) {
69 qreal left = r.x();
70 qreal right = r.x() + r.width();
71 qreal top = r.y();
72 qreal bottom = r.y() + r.height();
73 pts[0] = left;
74 pts[1] = top;
75 pts[2] = right;
76 pts[3] = top;
77 pts[4] = right;
78 pts[5] = bottom;
79 pts[6] = left;
80 pts[7] = bottom;
81 }
82 inline QRectVectorPath(const QRect &r)
83 : QVectorPath(pts, 4, nullptr, QVectorPath::RectangleHint | QVectorPath::ImplicitClose)
84 {
85 set(r);
86 }
87 inline QRectVectorPath(const QRectF &r)
88 : QVectorPath(pts, 4, nullptr, QVectorPath::RectangleHint | QVectorPath::ImplicitClose)
89 {
90 set(r);
91 }
92 inline QRectVectorPath()
93 : QVectorPath(pts, 4, nullptr, QVectorPath::RectangleHint | QVectorPath::ImplicitClose)
94 { }
95
96 qreal pts[8];
97};

172#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
173static const QRectF boundingRect(const QPointF *points, int pointCount)
174{
175 const QPointF *e = points;
176 const QPointF *last = points + pointCount;
177 qreal minx, maxx, miny, maxy;
178 minx = maxx = e->x();
179 miny = maxy = e->y();
180 while (++e < last) {
181 if (e->x() < minx)
182 minx = e->x();
183 else if (e->x() > maxx)
184 maxx = e->x();
185 if (e->y() < miny)
186 miny = e->y();
187 else if (e->y() > maxy)
188 maxy = e->y();
189 }
190 return QRectF(QPointF(minx, miny), QPointF(maxx, maxy));
191}
192#endif

241/*!
242 \class QRasterPaintEngine
243 \preliminary
244 \ingroup qws
245 \inmodule QtGui
246 \since 4.2
247
248 \brief The QRasterPaintEngine class enables hardware acceleration
249 of painting operations in Qt for Embedded Linux.
250
251 Note that this functionality is only available in
252 Qt for Embedded Linux.
253
254 In Qt for Embedded Linux, painting is a pure software
255 implementation. But starting with Qt 4.2, it is
256 possible to add an accelerated graphics driver to take advantage
257 of available hardware resources.
258
259 Hardware acceleration is accomplished by creating a custom screen
260 driver, accelerating the copying from memory to the screen, and
261 implementing a custom paint engine accelerating the various
262 painting operations. Then a custom paint device and a custom
263 window surface must be implemented to make
264 Qt for Embedded Linux aware of the accelerated driver.
265
266 \note The QRasterPaintEngine class does not support 8-bit images.
267 Instead, they need to be converted to a supported format, such as
268 QImage::Format_ARGB32_Premultiplied.
269
270 \sa QPaintEngine
271*/
272
273/*
274 \fn QPaintEngine::Type QRasterPaintEngine::type() const
275 \reimp
276*/
277

279 \since 4.5

283 {QPaintEngine::PaintEngineFeature}{paint engine features and

285*/

302
303void QRasterPaintEngine::init()
304{
305 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
306
307
308#ifdef Q_OS_WIN
309 d->hdc = 0;
310#endif
311
312 // The antialiasing raster.
313 d->grayRaster.reset(other: new QT_FT_Raster);
314 Q_CHECK_PTR(d->grayRaster.data());
315 if (qt_ft_grays_raster.raster_new(d->grayRaster.data()))
316 QT_THROW(std::bad_alloc()); // an error creating the raster is caused by a bad malloc
317
318
319 d->rasterizer.reset(other: new QRasterizer);
320 d->rasterBuffer.reset(other: new QRasterBuffer());
321 d->outlineMapper.reset(other: new QOutlineMapper);
322 d->outlinemapper_xform_dirty = true;
323
324 d->basicStroker.setMoveToHook(qt_ft_outline_move_to);
325 d->basicStroker.setLineToHook(qt_ft_outline_line_to);
326 d->basicStroker.setCubicToHook(qt_ft_outline_cubic_to);
327
328 d->baseClip.reset(other: new QClipData(d->device->height()));
329 d->baseClip->setClipRect(QRect(0, 0, d->device->width(), d->device->height()));
330
331 d->image_filler.init(rb: d->rasterBuffer.data(), pe: this);
332 d->image_filler.type = QSpanData::Texture;
333
334 d->image_filler_xform.init(rb: d->rasterBuffer.data(), pe: this);
335 d->image_filler_xform.type = QSpanData::Texture;
336
337 d->solid_color_filler.init(rb: d->rasterBuffer.data(), pe: this);
338 d->solid_color_filler.type = QSpanData::Solid;
339
340 d->deviceDepth = d->device->depth();
341
342 d->mono_surface = false;
343 gccaps &= ~PorterDuff;
344
345 QImage::Format format = QImage::Format_Invalid;
346
347 switch (d->device->devType()) {
348 case QInternal::Pixmap:
349 qWarning(msg: "QRasterPaintEngine: unsupported for pixmaps...");
350 break;
351 case QInternal::Image:
352 format = d->rasterBuffer->prepare(image: static_cast<QImage *>(d->device));
353 break;
354 default:
355 qWarning(msg: "QRasterPaintEngine: unsupported target device %d\n", d->device->devType());
356 d->device = nullptr;
357 return;
358 }
359
360 switch (format) {
361 case QImage::Format_MonoLSB:
362 case QImage::Format_Mono:
363 d->mono_surface = true;
364 break;
365 default:
366 if (QImage::toPixelFormat(format).alphaUsage() == QPixelFormat::UsesAlpha)
367 gccaps |= PorterDuff;
368 break;
369 }
370}

376QRasterPaintEngine::~QRasterPaintEngine()

378 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
379
380 qt_ft_grays_raster.raster_done(*d->grayRaster.data());
381}

383/*!
384 \reimp
385*/
386bool QRasterPaintEngine::begin(QPaintDevice *device)
387{
388 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
389
390 if (device->devType() == QInternal::Pixmap) {
391 QPixmap *pixmap = static_cast<QPixmap *>(device);
392 QPlatformPixmap *pd = pixmap->handle();
393 if (pd->classId() == QPlatformPixmap::RasterClass || pd->classId() == QPlatformPixmap::BlitterClass)
394 d->device = pd->buffer();
395 } else {
396 d->device = device;
397 }
398
399 // Make sure QPaintEngine::paintDevice() returns the proper device.
400 d->pdev = d->device;
401
402 Q_ASSERT(d->device->devType() == QInternal::Image
403 || d->device->devType() == QInternal::CustomRaster);
404
405 d->systemStateChanged();
406
407 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
408 ensureOutlineMapper();
409 d->outlineMapper->setClipRect(d->deviceRect);
410 d->rasterizer->setClipRect(d->deviceRect);
411
412 s->penData.init(rb: d->rasterBuffer.data(), pe: this);
413 s->penData.setup(brush: s->pen.brush(), alpha: s->intOpacity, compositionMode: s->composition_mode, isCosmetic: s->flags.cosmetic_brush);
414 s->stroker = &d->basicStroker;
415 d->basicStroker.setClipRect(d->deviceRect);
416
417 s->brushData.init(rb: d->rasterBuffer.data(), pe: this);
418 s->brushData.setup(brush: s->brush, alpha: s->intOpacity, compositionMode: s->composition_mode, isCosmetic: s->flags.cosmetic_brush);
419
420 d->rasterBuffer->compositionMode = QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver;
421
422 setDirty(DirtyBrushOrigin);
423
424#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
425 qDebug() << "QRasterPaintEngine::begin(" << (void *) device
426 << ") devType:" << device->devType()
427 << "devRect:" << d->deviceRect;
428 if (d->baseClip) {
429 dumpClip(d->rasterBuffer->width(), d->rasterBuffer->height(), &*d->baseClip);
430 }
431#endif
432
433 if (d->mono_surface)
434 d->glyphCacheFormat = QFontEngine::Format_Mono;
435#if defined(Q_OS_WIN)
436 else if (clearTypeFontsEnabled())
437#else
438 else if (false)
439#endif
440 {
441 QImage::Format format = static_cast<QImage *>(d->device)->format();
442 if (format == QImage::Format_ARGB32_Premultiplied || format == QImage::Format_RGB32)
443 d->glyphCacheFormat = QFontEngine::Format_A32;
444 else
445 d->glyphCacheFormat = QFontEngine::Format_A8;
446 } else
447 d->glyphCacheFormat = QFontEngine::Format_A8;
448
449 setActive(true);
450 return true;
451}
452
453/*!
454 \reimp
455*/
456bool QRasterPaintEngine::end()
457{
458#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
459 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
460 qDebug() << "QRasterPaintEngine::end devRect:" << d->deviceRect;
461 if (d->baseClip) {
462 dumpClip(d->rasterBuffer->width(), d->rasterBuffer->height(), &*d->baseClip);
463 }
464#endif
465
466 return true;
467}

593/*!
594 \internal
595*/
596void QRasterPaintEngine::updatePen(const QPen &pen)
597{
598 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
599 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
600#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
601 qDebug() << "QRasterPaintEngine::updatePen():" << s->pen;
602#endif
603
604 Qt::PenStyle pen_style = qpen_style(p: pen);
605
606 s->lastPen = pen;
607 s->strokeFlags = 0;
608
609 s->penData.clip = d->clip();
610 s->penData.setup(brush: pen_style == Qt::NoPen ? QBrush() : pen.brush(), alpha: s->intOpacity,
611 compositionMode: s->composition_mode, isCosmetic: s->flags.cosmetic_brush);
612
613 if (s->strokeFlags & QRasterPaintEngine::DirtyTransform
614 || pen.brush().transform().type() >= QTransform::TxNone) {
615 d->updateMatrixData(spanData: &s->penData, brush: pen.brush(), brushMatrix: s->matrix);
616 }
617
618 // Slightly ugly handling of an uncommon case... We need to change
619 // the pen because it is reused in draw_midpoint to decide dashed
620 // or non-dashed.
621 if (pen_style == Qt::CustomDashLine && pen.dashPattern().size() == 0) {
622 pen_style = Qt::SolidLine;
623 s->lastPen.setStyle(Qt::SolidLine);
624 }
625
626 d->basicStroker.setJoinStyle(qpen_joinStyle(p: pen));
627 d->basicStroker.setCapStyle(qpen_capStyle(p: pen));
628 d->basicStroker.setMiterLimit(pen.miterLimit());
629
630 qreal penWidth = qpen_widthf(p: pen);
631 if (penWidth == 0)
632 d->basicStroker.setStrokeWidth(1);
633 else
634 d->basicStroker.setStrokeWidth(penWidth);
635
636 if (pen_style == Qt::SolidLine) {
637 s->stroker = &d->basicStroker;
638 } else if (pen_style != Qt::NoPen) {
639 if (!d->dashStroker)
640 d->dashStroker.reset(other: new QDashStroker(&d->basicStroker));
641 if (pen.isCosmetic()) {
642 d->dashStroker->setClipRect(d->deviceRect);
643 } else {
644 // ### I've seen this inverted devrect multiple places now...
645 QRectF clipRect = s->matrix.inverted().mapRect(QRectF(d->deviceRect));
646 d->dashStroker->setClipRect(clipRect);
647 }
648 d->dashStroker->setDashPattern(pen.dashPattern());
649 d->dashStroker->setDashOffset(pen.dashOffset());
650 s->stroker = d->dashStroker.data();
651 } else {
652 s->stroker = nullptr;
653 }
654
655 ensureRasterState(); // needed because of tx_noshear...
656 bool cosmetic = pen.isCosmetic();
657 s->flags.fast_pen = pen_style > Qt::NoPen
658 && s->penData.blend
659 && ((cosmetic && penWidth <= 1)
660 || (!cosmetic && (s->flags.tx_noshear || !s->flags.antialiased) && penWidth * s->txscale <= 1));
661
662 s->flags.non_complex_pen = qpen_capStyle(p: s->lastPen) <= Qt::SquareCap && s->flags.tx_noshear;
663
664 s->strokeFlags = 0;
665}

698/*!
699 \internal
700*/
701void QRasterPaintEngine::updateBrush(const QBrush &brush)
702{
703#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
704 qDebug() << "QRasterPaintEngine::updateBrush()" << brush;
705#endif
706 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
707 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
708 // must set clip prior to setup, as setup uses it...
709 s->brushData.clip = d->clip();
710 s->brushData.setup(brush, alpha: s->intOpacity, compositionMode: s->composition_mode, isCosmetic: s->flags.cosmetic_brush);
711 if (s->fillFlags & DirtyTransform
712 || brush.transform().type() >= QTransform::TxNone)
713 d_func()->updateMatrixData(spanData: &s->brushData, brush, brushMatrix: d->brushMatrix());
714 s->lastBrush = brush;
715 s->fillFlags = 0;
716}

723
724void QRasterPaintEngine::updateRasterState()
725{
726 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
727
728 if (s->dirty & DirtyTransform)
729 updateMatrix(matrix: s->matrix);
730
731 if (s->dirty & (DirtyPen|DirtyCompositionMode|DirtyOpacity)) {
732 const QPainter::CompositionMode mode = s->composition_mode;
733 s->flags.fast_text = (s->penData.type == QSpanData::Solid)
734 && s->intOpacity == 256
735 && (mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver
736 || (mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source
737 && (s->penData.solidColor.spec() != QColor::ExtendedRgb &&
738 s->penData.solidColor.alphaF() >= 1.0f)));
739 }
740
741 s->dirty = 0;
742}

856
857void QRasterPaintEnginePrivate::drawImage(const QPointF &pt,
858 const QImage &img,
859 SrcOverBlendFunc func,
860 const QRect &clip,
861 int alpha,
862 const QRect &sr)
863{
864 if (alpha == 0 || !clip.isValid())
865 return;
866 if (pt.x() > qreal(clip.right()) || pt.y() > qreal(clip.bottom()))
867 return;
868 if ((pt.x() + img.width()) < qreal(clip.left()) || (pt.y() + img.height()) < qreal(clip.top()))
869 return;
870
871 Q_ASSERT(img.depth() >= 8);
872
873 qsizetype srcBPL = img.bytesPerLine();
874 const uchar *srcBits = img.bits();
875 int srcSize = img.depth() >> 3; // This is the part that is incompatible with lower than 8-bit..
876 int iw = img.width();
877 int ih = img.height();
878
879 if (!sr.isEmpty()) {
880 iw = sr.width();
881 ih = sr.height();
882 // Adjust the image according to the source offset...
883 srcBits += ((sr.y() * srcBPL) + sr.x() * srcSize);
884 }
885
886 // adapt the x parameters
887 int x = qRound(d: pt.x());
888 int cx1 = clip.x();
889 int cx2 = clip.x() + clip.width();
890 if (x < cx1) {
891 int d = cx1 - x;
892 srcBits += srcSize * d;
893 iw -= d;
894 x = cx1;
895 }
896 if (x + iw > cx2) {
897 int d = x + iw - cx2;
898 iw -= d;
899 }
900 if (iw <= 0)
901 return;
902
903 // adapt the y parameters...
904 int cy1 = clip.y();
905 int cy2 = clip.y() + clip.height();
906 int y = qRound(d: pt.y());
907 if (y < cy1) {
908 int d = cy1 - y;
909 srcBits += srcBPL * d;
910 ih -= d;
911 y = cy1;
912 }
913 if (y + ih > cy2) {
914 int d = y + ih - cy2;
915 ih -= d;
916 }
917 if (ih <= 0)
918 return;
919
920 // call the blend function...
921 int dstSize = rasterBuffer->bytesPerPixel();
922 qsizetype dstBPL = rasterBuffer->bytesPerLine();
923 func(rasterBuffer->buffer() + x * dstSize + y * dstBPL, dstBPL,
924 srcBits, srcBPL,
925 iw, ih,
926 alpha);
927}
928
929void QRasterPaintEnginePrivate::blitImage(const QPointF &pt,
930 const QImage &img,
931 const QRect &clip,
932 const QRect &sr)
933{
934 if (!clip.isValid())
935 return;
936 if (pt.x() > qreal(clip.right()) || pt.y() > qreal(clip.bottom()))
937 return;
938 if ((pt.x() + img.width()) < qreal(clip.left()) || (pt.y() + img.height()) < qreal(clip.top()))
939 return;
940
941 Q_ASSERT(img.depth() >= 8);
942
943 qsizetype srcBPL = img.bytesPerLine();
944 const uchar *srcBits = img.bits();
945 int srcSize = img.depth() >> 3; // This is the part that is incompatible with lower than 8-bit..
946 int iw = img.width();
947 int ih = img.height();
948
949 if (!sr.isEmpty()) {
950 iw = sr.width();
951 ih = sr.height();
952 // Adjust the image according to the source offset...
953 srcBits += ((sr.y() * srcBPL) + sr.x() * srcSize);
954 }
955
956 // adapt the x parameters
957 int x = qRound(d: pt.x());
958 int cx1 = clip.x();
959 int cx2 = clip.x() + clip.width();
960 if (x < cx1) {
961 int d = cx1 - x;
962 srcBits += srcSize * d;
963 iw -= d;
964 x = cx1;
965 }
966 if (x + iw > cx2) {
967 int d = x + iw - cx2;
968 iw -= d;
969 }
970 if (iw <= 0)
971 return;
972
973 // adapt the y parameters...
974 int cy1 = clip.y();
975 int cy2 = clip.y() + clip.height();
976 int y = qRound(d: pt.y());
977 if (y < cy1) {
978 int d = cy1 - y;
979 srcBits += srcBPL * d;
980 ih -= d;
981 y = cy1;
982 }
983 if (y + ih > cy2) {
984 int d = y + ih - cy2;
985 ih -= d;
986 }
987 if (ih <= 0)
988 return;
989
990 // blit..
991 int dstSize = rasterBuffer->bytesPerPixel();
992 qsizetype dstBPL = rasterBuffer->bytesPerLine();
993 const uint *src = (const uint *) srcBits;
994 uint *dst = reinterpret_cast<uint *>(rasterBuffer->buffer() + x * dstSize + y * dstBPL);
995
996 const int len = iw * (qt_depthForFormat(format: rasterBuffer->format) >> 3);
997 for (int y = 0; y < ih; ++y) {
998 memcpy(dest: dst, src: src, n: len);
999 dst = (quint32 *)(((uchar *) dst) + dstBPL);
1000 src = (const quint32 *)(((const uchar *) src) + srcBPL);
1001 }
1002}

1007 deviceRectUnclipped = QRect(0, 0,
1008 qMin(a: QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT, b: device->width()),

1021#endif

1033void QRasterPaintEnginePrivate::updateMatrixData(QSpanData *spanData, const QBrush &b, const QTransform &m)
1034{
1035 if (b.d->style == Qt::NoBrush || b.d->style == Qt::SolidPattern)
1036 return;
1037
1038 Q_Q(QRasterPaintEngine);
1039 bool bilinear = q->state()->flags.bilinear;
1040
1041 if (b.d->transform.type() > QTransform::TxNone) { // FALCON: optimize
1042 spanData->setupMatrix(matrix: b.transform() * m, bilinear);
1043 } else {
1044 if (m.type() <= QTransform::TxTranslate) {
1045 // specialize setupMatrix for translation matrices
1046 // to avoid needless matrix inversion
1047 spanData->m11 = 1;
1048 spanData->m12 = 0;
1049 spanData->m13 = 0;
1050 spanData->m21 = 0;
1051 spanData->m22 = 1;
1052 spanData->m23 = 0;
1053 spanData->m33 = 1;
1054 spanData->dx = -m.dx();
1055 spanData->dy = -m.dy();
1056 spanData->txop = m.type();
1057 spanData->bilinear = bilinear;
1058 spanData->fast_matrix = qAbs(t: m.dx()) < 1e4 && qAbs(t: m.dy()) < 1e4;
1059 spanData->adjustSpanMethods();
1060 } else {
1061 spanData->setupMatrix(matrix: m, bilinear);
1062 }
1063 }
1064}

1118/*!
1119 \internal
1120*/
1121void QRasterPaintEngine::clip(const QVectorPath &path, Qt::ClipOperation op)
1122{
1123#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
1124 qDebug() << "QRasterPaintEngine::clip(): " << path << op;
1125
1126 if (path.elements()) {
1127 for (int i=0; i<path.elementCount(); ++i) {
1128 qDebug() << " - " << path.elements()[i]
1129 << '(' << path.points()[i*2] << ", " << path.points()[i*2+1] << ')';
1130 }
1131 } else {
1132 for (int i=0; i<path.elementCount(); ++i) {
1133 qDebug() << " ---- "
1134 << '(' << path.points()[i*2] << ", " << path.points()[i*2+1] << ')';
1135 }
1136 }
1137#endif
1138
1139 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1140 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1141
1142 // There are some cases that are not supported by clip(QRect)
1143 if (op != Qt::IntersectClip || !s->clip || s->clip->hasRectClip || s->clip->hasRegionClip) {
1144 if (s->matrix.type() <= QTransform::TxScale
1145 && path.isRect()) {
1146#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
1147 qDebug(" --- optimizing vector clip to rect clip...");
1148#endif
1149 const qreal *points = path.points();
1150 QRectF r(points[0], points[1], points[4]-points[0], points[5]-points[1]);
1151 if (setClipRectInDeviceCoords(r: qt_mapFillRect(rect: r, xf: s->matrix), op))
1152 return;
1153 }
1154 }
1155
1156 if (op == Qt::NoClip) {
1157 qrasterpaintengine_state_setNoClip(s);
1158
1159 } else {
1160 QClipData *base = d->baseClip.data();
1161
1162 // Intersect with current clip when available...
1163 if (op == Qt::IntersectClip && s->clip)
1164 base = s->clip;
1165
1166 // We always intersect, except when there is nothing to
1167 // intersect with, in which case we simplify the operation to
1168 // a replace...
1169 Qt::ClipOperation isectOp = Qt::IntersectClip;
1170 if (base == nullptr)
1171 isectOp = Qt::ReplaceClip;
1172
1173 QClipData *newClip = new QClipData(d->rasterBuffer->height());
1174 newClip->initialize();
1175 ClipData clipData = { .oldClip: base, .newClip: newClip, .operation: isectOp };
1176 ensureOutlineMapper();
1177 d->rasterize(outline: d->outlineMapper->convertPath(path), callback: qt_span_clip, userData: &clipData, rasterBuffer: nullptr);
1178
1179 newClip->fixup();
1180
1181 if (s->flags.has_clip_ownership)
1182 delete s->clip;
1183
1184 s->clip = newClip;
1185 s->flags.has_clip_ownership = true;
1186 }
1187 qrasterpaintengine_dirty_clip(d, s);
1188}

1192/*!
1193 \internal
1194*/
1195void QRasterPaintEngine::clip(const QRect &rect, Qt::ClipOperation op)
1196{
1197#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
1198 qDebug() << "QRasterPaintEngine::clip(): " << rect << op;
1199#endif
1200
1201 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1202
1203 if (op == Qt::NoClip) {
1204 qrasterpaintengine_state_setNoClip(s);
1205
1206 } else if (s->matrix.type() > QTransform::TxScale) {
1207 QPaintEngineEx::clip(rect, op);
1208 return;
1209
1210 } else if (!setClipRectInDeviceCoords(r: qt_mapFillRect(rect, xf: s->matrix), op)) {
1211 QPaintEngineEx::clip(rect, op);
1212 return;
1213 }
1214}
1215
1216
1217bool QRasterPaintEngine::setClipRectInDeviceCoords(const QRect &r, Qt::ClipOperation op)
1218{
1219 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1220 QRect clipRect = r & d->deviceRect;
1221 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1222
1223 if (op == Qt::ReplaceClip || s->clip == nullptr) {
1224
1225 // No current clip, hence we intersect with sysclip and be
1226 // done with it...
1227 QRegion clipRegion = systemClip();
1228 QClipData *clip = new QClipData(d->rasterBuffer->height());
1229
1230 if (clipRegion.isEmpty())
1231 clip->setClipRect(clipRect);
1232 else
1233 clip->setClipRegion(clipRegion & clipRect);
1234
1235 if (s->flags.has_clip_ownership)
1236 delete s->clip;
1237
1238 s->clip = clip;
1239 s->clip->enabled = true;
1240 s->flags.has_clip_ownership = true;
1241
1242 } else if (op == Qt::IntersectClip){ // intersect clip with current clip
1243 QClipData *base = s->clip;
1244
1245 Q_ASSERT(base);
1246 if (base->hasRectClip || base->hasRegionClip) {
1247 if (!s->flags.has_clip_ownership) {
1248 s->clip = new QClipData(d->rasterBuffer->height());
1249 s->flags.has_clip_ownership = true;
1250 }
1251 if (base->hasRectClip)
1252 s->clip->setClipRect(base->clipRect & clipRect);
1253 else
1254 s->clip->setClipRegion(base->clipRegion & clipRect);
1255 s->clip->enabled = true;
1256 } else {
1257 return false;
1258 }
1259 } else {
1260 return false;
1261 }
1262
1263 qrasterpaintengine_dirty_clip(d, s);
1264 return true;
1265}

1268/*!
1269 \internal
1270*/
1271void QRasterPaintEngine::clip(const QRegion &region, Qt::ClipOperation op)
1272{
1273#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
1274 qDebug() << "QRasterPaintEngine::clip(): " << region << op;
1275#endif
1276
1277 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1278
1279 if (region.rectCount() == 1) {
1280 clip(rect: region.boundingRect(), op);
1281 return;
1282 }
1283
1284 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1285 const QClipData *clip = d->clip();
1286 const QClipData *baseClip = d->baseClip.data();
1287
1288 if (op == Qt::NoClip) {
1289 qrasterpaintengine_state_setNoClip(s);
1290 } else if (s->matrix.type() > QTransform::TxScale
1291 || (op == Qt::IntersectClip && !clip->hasRectClip && !clip->hasRegionClip)
1292 || (op == Qt::ReplaceClip && !baseClip->hasRectClip && !baseClip->hasRegionClip)) {
1293 QPaintEngineEx::clip(region, op);
1294 } else {
1295 const QClipData *curClip;
1296 QClipData *newClip;
1297
1298 if (op == Qt::IntersectClip)
1299 curClip = clip;
1300 else
1301 curClip = baseClip;
1302
1303 if (s->flags.has_clip_ownership) {
1304 newClip = s->clip;
1305 Q_ASSERT(newClip);
1306 } else {
1307 newClip = new QClipData(d->rasterBuffer->height());
1308 s->clip = newClip;
1309 s->flags.has_clip_ownership = true;
1310 }
1311
1312 QRegion r = s->matrix.map(r: region);
1313 if (curClip->hasRectClip)
1314 newClip->setClipRegion(r & curClip->clipRect);
1315 else if (curClip->hasRegionClip)
1316 newClip->setClipRegion(r & curClip->clipRegion);
1317
1318 qrasterpaintengine_dirty_clip(d, s);
1319 }
1320}

1329/*!
1330 \internal
1331*/
1332void QRasterPaintEngine::fillPath(const QPainterPath &path, QSpanData *fillData)
1333{
1334#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
1335 qDebug() << " --- fillPath, bounds=" << path.boundingRect();
1336#endif
1337
1338 if (!fillData->blend)
1339 return;
1340
1341 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1342
1343 const QRectF controlPointRect = path.controlPointRect();
1344
1345 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1346 const QRect deviceRect = s->matrix.mapRect(controlPointRect).toRect();
1347 ProcessSpans blend = d->getBrushFunc(rect: deviceRect, data: fillData);
1348 const bool do_clip = (deviceRect.left() < -QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT
1349 || deviceRect.right() > QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT
1350 || deviceRect.top() < -QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT
1351 || deviceRect.bottom() > QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT);
1352
1353 if (!s->flags.antialiased && !do_clip) {
1354 d->initializeRasterizer(data: fillData);
1355 d->rasterizer->rasterize(path: path * s->matrix, fillRule: path.fillRule());
1356 return;
1357 }
1358
1359 ensureOutlineMapper();
1360 d->rasterize(outline: d->outlineMapper->convertPath(path), callback: blend, spanData: fillData, rasterBuffer: d->rasterBuffer.data());
1361}
1362
1363static void fillRect_normalized(const QRect &r, QSpanData *data,
1364 QRasterPaintEnginePrivate *pe)
1365{
1366 int x1, x2, y1, y2;
1367
1368 bool rectClipped = true;
1369
1370 if (data->clip) {
1371 x1 = qMax(a: r.x(), b: data->clip->xmin);
1372 x2 = qMin(a: r.x() + r.width(), b: data->clip->xmax);
1373 y1 = qMax(a: r.y(), b: data->clip->ymin);
1374 y2 = qMin(a: r.y() + r.height(), b: data->clip->ymax);
1375 rectClipped = data->clip->hasRectClip;
1376
1377 } else if (pe) {
1378 x1 = qMax(a: r.x(), b: pe->deviceRect.x());
1379 x2 = qMin(a: r.x() + r.width(), b: pe->deviceRect.x() + pe->deviceRect.width());
1380 y1 = qMax(a: r.y(), b: pe->deviceRect.y());
1381 y2 = qMin(a: r.y() + r.height(), b: pe->deviceRect.y() + pe->deviceRect.height());
1382 } else {
1383 x1 = qMax(a: r.x(), b: 0);
1384 x2 = qMin(a: r.x() + r.width(), b: data->rasterBuffer->width());
1385 y1 = qMax(a: r.y(), b: 0);
1386 y2 = qMin(a: r.y() + r.height(), b: data->rasterBuffer->height());
1387 }
1388
1389 if (x2 <= x1 || y2 <= y1)
1390 return;
1391
1392 const int width = x2 - x1;
1393 const int height = y2 - y1;
1394
1395 bool isUnclipped = rectClipped
1396 || (pe && pe->isUnclipped_normalized(rect: QRect(x1, y1, width, height)));
1397
1398 if (pe && isUnclipped) {
1399 const QPainter::CompositionMode mode = pe->rasterBuffer->compositionMode;
1400
1401 if (data->fillRect && (mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source
1402 || (mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver
1403 && (data->solidColor.spec() != QColor::ExtendedRgb &&
1404 data->solidColor.alphaF() >= 1.0f))))
1405 {
1406 data->fillRect(data->rasterBuffer, x1, y1, width, height, data->solidColor.rgba64());
1407 return;
1408 }
1409 }
1410
1411 ProcessSpans blend = isUnclipped ? data->unclipped_blend : data->blend;
1412
1413 const int nspans = 512;
1414 QT_FT_Span spans[nspans];
1415
1416 Q_ASSERT(data->blend);
1417 int y = y1;
1418 while (y < y2) {
1419 int n = qMin(a: nspans, b: y2 - y);
1420 int i = 0;
1421 while (i < n) {
1422 spans[i].x = x1;
1423 spans[i].len = width;
1424 spans[i].y = y + i;
1425 spans[i].coverage = 255;
1426 ++i;
1427 }
1428
1429 blend(n, spans, data);
1430 y += n;
1431 }
1432}

1436*/
1437void QRasterPaintEngine::drawRects(const QRect *rects, int rectCount)
1438{
1439#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
1440 qDebug(" - QRasterPaintEngine::drawRect(), rectCount=%d", rectCount);
1441#endif
1442 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1443 ensureRasterState();
1444 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1445
1446 // Fill
1447 ensureBrush();
1448 if (s->brushData.blend) {
1449 if (!s->flags.antialiased && s->matrix.type() <= QTransform::TxTranslate) {
1450 const QRect *r = rects;
1451 const QRect *lastRect = rects + rectCount;
1452

1454 int offset_y = int(s->matrix.dy());
1455 while (r < lastRect) {
1456 QRect rect = r->normalized();
1457 QRect rr = rect.translated(dx: offset_x, dy: offset_y);
1458 fillRect_normalized(r: rr, data: &s->brushData, pe: d);
1459 ++r;
1460 }
1461 } else {
1462 QRectVectorPath path;
1463 for (int i=0; i<rectCount; ++i) {
1464 path.set(rects[i]);
1465 fill(path, brush: s->brush);
1466 }
1467 }
1468 }
1469
1470 ensurePen();
1471 if (s->penData.blend) {
1472 QRectVectorPath path;
1473 if (s->flags.fast_pen) {
1474 QCosmeticStroker stroker(s, d->deviceRect, d->deviceRectUnclipped);
1475 for (int i = 0; i < rectCount; ++i) {
1476 path.set(rects[i]);
1477 stroker.drawPath(path);
1478 }
1479 } else {
1480 for (int i = 0; i < rectCount; ++i) {
1481 path.set(rects[i]);
1482 stroke(path, pen: s->pen);
1483 }
1484 }
1485 }
1486}

1540/*!
1541 \internal
1542*/
1543void QRasterPaintEngine::stroke(const QVectorPath &path, const QPen &pen)
1544{
1545 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1546 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1547
1548 ensurePen(pen);
1549 if (!s->penData.blend)
1550 return;
1551
1552 if (s->flags.fast_pen) {
1553 QCosmeticStroker stroker(s, d->deviceRect, d->deviceRectUnclipped);
1554 stroker.drawPath(path);
1555 } else if (s->flags.non_complex_pen && path.shape() == QVectorPath::LinesHint) {
1556 qreal width = s->lastPen.isCosmetic()
1557 ? (qpen_widthf(p: s->lastPen) == 0 ? 1 : qpen_widthf(p: s->lastPen))
1558 : qpen_widthf(p: s->lastPen) * s->txscale;
1559 int dashIndex = 0;
1560 qreal dashOffset = s->lastPen.dashOffset();
1561 bool inDash = true;
1562 qreal patternLength = 0;
1563 const QList<qreal> pattern = s->lastPen.dashPattern();
1564 for (int i = 0; i < pattern.size(); ++i)
1565 patternLength += pattern.at(i);
1566
1567 if (patternLength > 0) {
1568 dashOffset = std::fmod(x: dashOffset, y: patternLength);
1569 if (dashOffset < 0)
1570 dashOffset += patternLength;
1571 while (dashOffset >= pattern.at(i: dashIndex)) {
1572 dashOffset -= pattern.at(i: dashIndex);
1573 if (++dashIndex >= pattern.size())
1574 dashIndex = 0;
1575 inDash = !inDash;
1576 }
1577 }
1578
1579 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1580 d->initializeRasterizer(data: &s->penData);
1581 int lineCount = path.elementCount() / 2;
1582 const QLineF *lines = reinterpret_cast<const QLineF *>(path.points());
1583
1584 for (int i = 0; i < lineCount; ++i) {
1585 const QLineF line = s->matrix.map(l: lines[i]);
1586 if (line.p1() == line.p2()) {
1587 if (s->lastPen.capStyle() != Qt::FlatCap) {
1588 QPointF p = lines[i].p1();
1589 QLineF mappedline = s->matrix.map(l: QLineF(QPointF(p.x() - width*0.5, p.y()),
1590 QPointF(p.x() + width*0.5, p.y())));
1591 d->rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a: mappedline.p1(), b: mappedline.p2(),
1592 width: width / mappedline.length());
1593 }
1594 continue;
1595 }
1596
1597 if (qpen_style(p: s->lastPen) == Qt::SolidLine) {
1598 d->rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a: line.p1(), b: line.p2(),
1599 width: width / line.length(),
1600 squareCap: s->lastPen.capStyle() == Qt::SquareCap);
1601 } else {
1602 // LinesHint means each line is distinct, so restart dashing
1603 int dIndex = dashIndex;
1604 qreal dOffset = dashOffset;
1605 bool inD = inDash;
1606 d->rasterizeLine_dashed(line, width, dashIndex: &dIndex, dashOffset: &dOffset, inDash: &inD);
1607 }
1608 }
1609 }
1610 else
1611 QPaintEngineEx::stroke(path, pen);
1612}
1613
1614QRect QRasterPaintEngine::toNormalizedFillRect(const QRectF &rect)
1615{
1616 int x1 = qRound(d: rect.x());
1617 int y1 = qRound(d: rect.y());
1618 int x2 = qRound(d: rect.right());
1619 int y2 = qRound(d: rect.bottom());
1620
1621 if (x2 < x1)
1622 qSwap(value1&: x1, value2&: x2);
1623 if (y2 < y1)
1624 qSwap(value1&: y1, value2&: y2);
1625
1626 return QRect(x1, y1, x2 - x1, y2 - y1);
1627}

1629/*!
1630 \internal
1631*/
1632void QRasterPaintEngine::fill(const QVectorPath &path, const QBrush &brush)
1633{
1634 if (path.isEmpty())
1635 return;
1636#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
1637 QRectF rf = path.controlPointRect();
1638 qDebug() << "QRasterPaintEngine::fill(): "
1639 << "size=" << path.elementCount()
1640 << ", hints=" << Qt::hex << path.hints()
1641 << rf << brush;
1642#endif
1643
1644 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1645 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1646
1647 ensureBrush(brush);
1648 if (!s->brushData.blend)
1649 return;
1650
1651 if (path.shape() == QVectorPath::RectangleHint) {
1652 if (!s->flags.antialiased && s->matrix.type() <= QTransform::TxScale) {
1653 const qreal *p = path.points();
1654 QPointF tl = QPointF(p[0], p[1]) * s->matrix;
1655 QPointF br = QPointF(p[4], p[5]) * s->matrix;
1656 fillRect_normalized(r: toNormalizedFillRect(rect: QRectF(tl, br)), data: &s->brushData, pe: d);
1657 return;
1658 }
1659 ensureRasterState();
1660 if (s->flags.tx_noshear) {
1661 d->initializeRasterizer(data: &s->brushData);
1662 // ### Is normalizing really necessary here?
1663 const qreal *p = path.points();
1664 QRectF r = QRectF(p[0], p[1], p[2] - p[0], p[7] - p[1]).normalized();
1665 if (!r.isEmpty()) {
1666 const QPointF a = s->matrix.map(p: (r.topLeft() + r.bottomLeft()) * 0.5f);
1667 const QPointF b = s->matrix.map(p: (r.topRight() + r.bottomRight()) * 0.5f);
1668 d->rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a, b, width: r.height() / r.width());
1669 }
1670 return;
1671 }
1672 }
1673
1674 // ### Optimize for non transformed ellipses and rectangles...
1675 QRectF cpRect = path.controlPointRect();
1676 const QRectF pathDeviceRect = s->matrix.mapRect(cpRect);
1677 // Skip paths that by conservative estimates are completely outside the paint device.
1678 if (!pathDeviceRect.intersects(r: QRectF(d->deviceRect)) || !pathDeviceRect.isValid())
1679 return;
1680
1681 ProcessSpans blend = d->getBrushFunc(rect: pathDeviceRect, data: &s->brushData);
1682
1683 // ### Falcon
1684// const bool do_clip = (deviceRect.left() < -QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT
1685// || deviceRect.right() > QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT
1686// || deviceRect.top() < -QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT
1687// || deviceRect.bottom() > QT_RASTER_COORD_LIMIT);
1688
1689 // ### Falonc: implement....
1690// if (!s->flags.antialiased && !do_clip) {
1691// d->initializeRasterizer(&s->brushData);
1692// d->rasterizer->rasterize(path * d->matrix, path.fillRule());
1693// return;
1694// }
1695
1696 ensureOutlineMapper();
1697 d->rasterize(outline: d->outlineMapper->convertPath(path), callback: blend, spanData: &s->brushData, rasterBuffer: d->rasterBuffer.data());
1698}

1700void QRasterPaintEngine::fillRect(const QRectF &r, QSpanData *data)
1701{
1702 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1703 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1704
1705 if (!s->flags.antialiased) {
1706 uint txop = s->matrix.type();
1707 if (txop == QTransform::TxNone) {
1708 fillRect_normalized(r: toNormalizedFillRect(rect: r), data, pe: d);
1709 return;
1710 } else if (txop == QTransform::TxTranslate) {
1711 const QRect rr = toNormalizedFillRect(rect: r.translated(dx: s->matrix.dx(), dy: s->matrix.dy()));
1712 fillRect_normalized(r: rr, data, pe: d);
1713 return;
1714 } else if (txop == QTransform::TxScale) {
1715 const QRect rr = toNormalizedFillRect(rect: s->matrix.mapRect(r));
1716 fillRect_normalized(r: rr, data, pe: d);
1717 return;
1718 }
1719 }
1720 ensureRasterState();
1721 if (s->flags.tx_noshear) {
1722 d->initializeRasterizer(data);
1723 QRectF nr = r.normalized();
1724 if (!nr.isEmpty()) {
1725 const QPointF a = s->matrix.map(p: (nr.topLeft() + nr.bottomLeft()) * 0.5f);
1726 const QPointF b = s->matrix.map(p: (nr.topRight() + nr.bottomRight()) * 0.5f);
1727 d->rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a, b, width: nr.height() / nr.width());
1728 }
1729 return;
1730 }
1731
1732 QPainterPath path;
1733 path.addRect(rect: r);
1734 ensureOutlineMapper();
1735 fillPath(path, fillData: data);
1736}

1755static QColor qPremultiplyWithExtraAlpha(const QColor &c, int alpha)
1756{
1757 if (alpha == 0)
1758 return Qt::transparent;
1759 if (c.spec() == QColor::ExtendedRgb) {
1760 float r, g, b, a;
1761 c.getRgbF(r: &r, g: &g, b: &b, a: &a);
1762 a = a * alpha * (1.f / 256.f);
1763 return QColor::fromRgbF(r: r * a, g: g * a, b: b * a, a);
1764 }
1765 return qPremultiply(c: combineAlpha256(rgba64: c.rgba64(), alpha256: alpha));
1766}

1790static inline bool isAbove(const QPointF *a, const QPointF *b)
1791{
1792 return a->y() < b->y();
1793}
1794
1795static bool splitPolygon(const QPointF *points, int pointCount, QList<QPointF> *upper, QList<QPointF> *lower)
1796{
1797 Q_ASSERT(upper);
1798 Q_ASSERT(lower);
1799
1800 Q_ASSERT(pointCount >= 2);
1801
1802 QList<const QPointF *> sorted;
1803 sorted.reserve(size: pointCount);
1804
1805 upper->reserve(size: pointCount * 3 / 4);
1806 lower->reserve(size: pointCount * 3 / 4);
1807
1808 for (int i = 0; i < pointCount; ++i)
1809 sorted << points + i;
1810
1811 std::sort(first: sorted.begin(), last: sorted.end(), comp: isAbove);
1812
1813 qreal splitY = sorted.at(i: sorted.size() / 2)->y();
1814
1815 const QPointF *end = points + pointCount;
1816 const QPointF *last = end - 1;
1817
1818 QList<QPointF> *bin[2] = { upper, lower };
1819
1820 for (const QPointF *p = points; p < end; ++p) {
1821 int side = p->y() < splitY;
1822 int lastSide = last->y() < splitY;
1823
1824 if (side != lastSide) {
1825 if (qFuzzyCompare(p1: p->y(), p2: splitY)) {
1826 bin[!side]->append(t: *p);
1827 } else if (qFuzzyCompare(p1: last->y(), p2: splitY)) {
1828 bin[side]->append(t: *last);
1829 } else {
1830 QPointF delta = *p - *last;
1831 QPointF intersection(p->x() + delta.x() * (splitY - p->y()) / delta.y(), splitY);
1832
1833 bin[0]->append(t: intersection);
1834 bin[1]->append(t: intersection);
1835 }
1836 }
1837
1838 bin[side]->append(t: *p);
1839
1840 last = p;
1841 }
1842
1843 // give up if we couldn't reduce the point count
1844 return upper->size() < pointCount && lower->size() < pointCount;
1845}

1847/*!
1848 \internal
1849 */
1850void QRasterPaintEngine::fillPolygon(const QPointF *points, int pointCount, PolygonDrawMode mode)
1851{
1852 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1853 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1854
1855 const int maxPoints = 0xffff;
1856
1857 // max amount of points that raster engine can reliably handle
1858 if (pointCount > maxPoints) {
1859 QList<QPointF> upper, lower;
1860
1861 if (splitPolygon(points, pointCount, upper: &upper, lower: &lower)) {
1862 fillPolygon(points: upper.constData(), pointCount: upper.size(), mode);
1863 fillPolygon(points: lower.constData(), pointCount: lower.size(), mode);
1864 } else
1865 qWarning(msg: "Polygon too complex for filling.");
1866
1867 return;
1868 }
1869
1870 // Compose polygon fill..,
1871 QVectorPath vp((const qreal *) points, pointCount, nullptr, QVectorPath::polygonFlags(mode));
1872 ensureOutlineMapper();
1873 QT_FT_Outline *outline = d->outlineMapper->convertPath(path: vp);
1874
1875 // scanconvert.
1876 ProcessSpans brushBlend = d->getBrushFunc(rect: d->outlineMapper->controlPointRect,
1877 data: &s->brushData);
1878 d->rasterize(outline, callback: brushBlend, spanData: &s->brushData, rasterBuffer: d->rasterBuffer.data());
1879}

1884void QRasterPaintEngine::drawPolygon(const QPointF *points, int pointCount, PolygonDrawMode mode)
1885{
1886 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);

1891 for (int i=0; i<pointCount; ++i)

1895
1896 if (mode != PolylineMode && QVectorPath::isRect(pts: (const qreal *) points, elementCount: pointCount)) {
1897 QRectF r(points[0], points[2]);
1898 drawRects(rects: &r, rectCount: 1);
1899 return;
1900 }
1901
1902 ensurePen();
1903 if (mode != PolylineMode) {
1904 // Do the fill...
1905 ensureBrush();
1906 if (s->brushData.blend)
1907 fillPolygon(points, pointCount, mode);
1908 }
1909
1910 // Do the outline...
1911 if (s->penData.blend) {
1912 QVectorPath vp((const qreal *) points, pointCount, nullptr, QVectorPath::polygonFlags(mode));
1913 if (s->flags.fast_pen) {
1914 QCosmeticStroker stroker(s, d->deviceRect, d->deviceRectUnclipped);
1915 stroker.drawPath(path: vp);

1922/*!
1923 \reimp
1924*/
1925void QRasterPaintEngine::drawPolygon(const QPoint *points, int pointCount, PolygonDrawMode mode)
1926{
1927 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
1928 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
1929
1930#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
1931 qDebug(" - QRasterPaintEngine::drawPolygon(I), pointCount=%d", pointCount);
1932 for (int i=0; i<pointCount; ++i)
1933 qDebug() << " - " << points[i];
1934#endif
1935 Q_ASSERT(pointCount >= 2);
1936 if (mode != PolylineMode && QVectorPath::isRect(pts: (const int *) points, elementCount: pointCount)) {
1937 QRect r(points[0].x(),
1938 points[0].y(),
1939 points[2].x() - points[0].x(),
1940 points[2].y() - points[0].y());
1941 drawRects(rects: &r, rectCount: 1);
1942 return;
1943 }
1944
1945 ensurePen();
1946
1947 // Do the fill
1948 if (mode != PolylineMode) {
1949 ensureBrush();
1950 if (s->brushData.blend) {
1951 // Compose polygon fill..,
1952 ensureOutlineMapper();
1953 d->outlineMapper->beginOutline(fillRule: mode == WindingMode ? Qt::WindingFill : Qt::OddEvenFill);
1954 d->outlineMapper->moveTo(pt: *points);
1955 const QPoint *p = points;
1956 const QPoint *ep = points + pointCount - 1;
1957 do {
1958 d->outlineMapper->lineTo(pt: *(++p));
1959 } while (p < ep);
1960 d->outlineMapper->endOutline();
1961
1962 // scanconvert.
1963 ProcessSpans brushBlend = d->getBrushFunc(rect: d->outlineMapper->controlPointRect,
1964 data: &s->brushData);
1965 d->rasterize(outline: d->outlineMapper->outline(), callback: brushBlend, spanData: &s->brushData, rasterBuffer: d->rasterBuffer.data());
1966 }
1967 }
1968
1969 // Do the outline...
1970 if (s->penData.blend) {
1971 int count = pointCount * 2;
1972 QVarLengthArray<qreal> fpoints(count);
1973 for (int i=0; i<count; ++i)
1974 fpoints[i] = ((const int *) points)[i];
1975 QVectorPath vp((qreal *) fpoints.data(), pointCount, nullptr, QVectorPath::polygonFlags(mode));
1976
1977 if (s->flags.fast_pen) {
1978 QCosmeticStroker stroker(s, d->deviceRect, d->deviceRectUnclipped);
1979 stroker.drawPath(path: vp);
1980 } else {
1981 QPaintEngineEx::stroke(path: vp, pen: s->lastPen);
1982 }
1983 }

2029*/
2030void QRasterPaintEngine::drawPixmap(const QRectF &r, const QPixmap &pixmap, const QRectF &sr)
2031{
2032#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
2033 qDebug() << " - QRasterPaintEngine::drawPixmap(), r=" << r << " sr=" << sr << " pixmap=" << pixmap.size() << "depth=" << pixmap.depth();
2034#endif
2035
2036 QPlatformPixmap* pd = pixmap.handle();
2037 if (pd->classId() == QPlatformPixmap::RasterClass) {
2038 const QImage &image = static_cast<QRasterPlatformPixmap *>(pd)->image;
2039 if (image.depth() == 1) {
2040 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
2041 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
2042 if (s->matrix.type() <= QTransform::TxTranslate
2043 && r.size() == sr.size()
2044 && r.size() == pixmap.size()) {
2045 ensurePen();
2046 drawBitmap(pos: r.topLeft() + QPointF(s->matrix.dx(), s->matrix.dy()), image, fill: &s->penData);
2047 return;
2048 } else {
2049 drawImage(r, pm: d->rasterBuffer->colorizeBitmap(image, color: s->pen.color()), sr);
2050 }
2051 } else {
2052 drawImage(r, pm: image, sr);
2053 }
2054 } else {
2055 QRect clippedSource = sr.toAlignedRect().intersected(other: pixmap.rect());
2056 const QImage image = pd->toImage(rect: clippedSource);
2057 QRectF translatedSource = sr.translated(p: -clippedSource.topLeft());
2058 if (image.depth() == 1) {
2059 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
2060 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
2061 if (s->matrix.type() <= QTransform::TxTranslate
2062 && r.size() == sr.size()
2063 && r.size() == pixmap.size()) {
2064 ensurePen();
2065 drawBitmap(pos: r.topLeft() + QPointF(s->matrix.dx(), s->matrix.dy()), image, fill: &s->penData);
2066 return;
2067 } else {
2068 drawImage(r, pm: d->rasterBuffer->colorizeBitmap(image, color: s->pen.color()), sr: translatedSource);
2069 }
2070 } else {
2071 drawImage(r, pm: image, sr: translatedSource);
2072 }
2073 }
2074}

2076static inline int fast_ceil_positive(const qreal &v)
2077{
2078 const int iv = int(v);
2079 if (v - iv == 0)
2080 return iv;
2081 else
2082 return iv + 1;
2083}
2084
2085static inline const QRect toAlignedRect_positive(const QRectF &rect)
2086{
2087 const int xmin = int(rect.x());
2088 const int xmax = int(fast_ceil_positive(v: rect.right()));
2089 const int ymin = int(rect.y());
2090 const int ymax = int(fast_ceil_positive(v: rect.bottom()));
2091 return QRect(xmin, ymin, xmax - xmin, ymax - ymin);
2092}

2097void QRasterPaintEngine::drawImage(const QPointF &p, const QImage &img)
2098{

2101#endif
2102
2103 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
2104 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
2105 qreal scale = img.devicePixelRatio();
2106
2107 if (scale > 1.0 || s->matrix.type() > QTransform::TxTranslate) {
2108 drawImage(r: QRectF(p.x(), p.y(), img.width() / scale, img.height() / scale),
2109 pm: img,
2110 sr: QRectF(0, 0, img.width(), img.height()));
2111 } else {
2112
2113 const QClipData *clip = d->clip();
2114 QPointF pt(p.x() + s->matrix.dx(), p.y() + s->matrix.dy());

2117 if (!clip) {

2119 return;
2120 } else if (clip->hasRectClip) {
2121 d->blitImage(pt, img, clip: clip->clipRect);
2122 return;
2123 }
2124 } else if (d->canUseFastImageBlending(mode: d->rasterBuffer->compositionMode, image: img)) {

2126 if (func) {

2128 d->drawImage(pt, img, func, clip: d->deviceRect, alpha: s->intOpacity);
2129 return;

2131 d->drawImage(pt, img, func, clip: clip->clipRect, alpha: s->intOpacity);
2132 return;
2133 }
2134 }

2136
2137

2157namespace {
2158 enum RotationType {
2159 Rotation90,
2160 Rotation180,
2161 Rotation270,
2162 NoRotation
2163 };
2164
2165 inline RotationType qRotationType(const QTransform &transform)
2166 {
2167 QTransform::TransformationType type = transform.type();
2168
2169 if (type > QTransform::TxRotate)
2170 return NoRotation;
2171
2172 if (type == QTransform::TxRotate && qFuzzyIsNull(d: transform.m11()) && qFuzzyCompare(p1: transform.m12(), p2: qreal(-1))
2173 && qFuzzyCompare(p1: transform.m21(), p2: qreal(1)) && qFuzzyIsNull(d: transform.m22()))
2174 return Rotation90;
2175
2176 if (type == QTransform::TxScale && qFuzzyCompare(p1: transform.m11(), p2: qreal(-1)) && qFuzzyIsNull(d: transform.m12())
2177 && qFuzzyIsNull(d: transform.m21()) && qFuzzyCompare(p1: transform.m22(), p2: qreal(-1)))
2178 return Rotation180;
2179
2180 if (type == QTransform::TxRotate && qFuzzyIsNull(d: transform.m11()) && qFuzzyCompare(p1: transform.m12(), p2: qreal(1))
2181 && qFuzzyCompare(p1: transform.m21(), p2: qreal(-1)) && qFuzzyIsNull(d: transform.m22()))
2182 return Rotation270;
2183
2184 return NoRotation;
2185 }

2197/*!
2198 \reimp
2199*/
2200void QRasterPaintEngine::drawImage(const QRectF &r, const QImage &img, const QRectF &sr,
2201 Qt::ImageConversionFlags)
2202{
2203#ifdef QT_DEBUG_DRAW
2204 qDebug() << " - QRasterPaintEngine::drawImage(), r=" << r << " sr=" << sr << " image=" << img.size() << "depth=" << img.depth();
2205#endif
2206
2207 if (r.isEmpty())
2208 return;
2209
2210 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
2211 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
2212 Q_ASSERT(s);
2213 int sr_l = qFloor(v: sr.left());
2214 int sr_r = qCeil(v: sr.right()) - 1;
2215 int sr_t = qFloor(v: sr.top());
2216 int sr_b = qCeil(v: sr.bottom()) - 1;
2217
2218 if (s->matrix.type() <= QTransform::TxScale && !s->flags.antialiased && sr_l == sr_r && sr_t == sr_b) {
2219 // as fillRect will apply the aliased coordinate delta we need to
2220 // subtract it here as we don't use it for image drawing
2221 QTransform old = s->matrix;
2222
2223 // Do whatever fillRect() does, but without premultiplying the color if it's already premultiplied.
2224 QRgb color = img.pixel(x: sr_l, y: sr_t);
2225 switch (img.format()) {
2226 case QImage::Format_ARGB32_Premultiplied:
2227 case QImage::Format_ARGB8565_Premultiplied:
2228 case QImage::Format_ARGB6666_Premultiplied:
2229 case QImage::Format_ARGB8555_Premultiplied:
2230 case QImage::Format_ARGB4444_Premultiplied:
2231 case QImage::Format_RGBA8888_Premultiplied:
2232 case QImage::Format_A2BGR30_Premultiplied:
2233 case QImage::Format_A2RGB30_Premultiplied:
2234 // Combine premultiplied color with the opacity set on the painter.
2235 d->solid_color_filler.solidColor = multiplyAlpha256(rgba64: QRgba64::fromArgb32(rgb: color), alpha256: s->intOpacity);
2236 break;
2237 default:
2238 d->solid_color_filler.solidColor = qPremultiply(c: combineAlpha256(rgba64: QRgba64::fromArgb32(rgb: color), alpha256: s->intOpacity));
2239 break;
2240 }
2241
2242 if (d->solid_color_filler.solidColor.alphaF() <= 0.0f && s->composition_mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver)
2243 return;
2244
2245 d->solid_color_filler.clip = d->clip();
2246 d->solid_color_filler.adjustSpanMethods();
2247 fillRect(r, data: &d->solid_color_filler);
2248
2249 s->matrix = old;
2250 return;
2251 }
2252
2253 bool stretch_sr = r.width() != sr.width() || r.height() != sr.height();
2254
2255 const QClipData *clip = d->clip();
2256
2257 if (s->matrix.type() == QTransform::TxRotate
2258 && !stretch_sr
2259 && (!clip || clip->hasRectClip)
2260 && s->intOpacity == 256
2261 && (d->rasterBuffer->compositionMode == QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver
2262 || d->rasterBuffer->compositionMode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source))
2263 {
2264 RotationType rotationType = qRotationType(transform: s->matrix);
2265 Q_ASSUME(d->rasterBuffer->format < QImage::NImageFormats);
2266 const QPixelLayout::BPP plBpp = qPixelLayouts[d->rasterBuffer->format].bpp;
2267
2268 if (rotationType != NoRotation && qMemRotateFunctions[plBpp][rotationType] && img.rect().contains(r: sr.toAlignedRect())) {
2269 QRectF transformedTargetRect = s->matrix.mapRect(r);
2270
2271 if (d->canUseImageBlitting(mode: d->rasterBuffer->compositionMode, image: img, pt: transformedTargetRect.topRight(), sr)) {
2272 QRect clippedTransformedTargetRect = transformedTargetRect.toRect().intersected(other: clip ? clip->clipRect : d->deviceRect);
2273 if (clippedTransformedTargetRect.isNull())
2274 return;
2275
2276 QRectF clippedTargetRect = s->matrix.inverted().mapRect(QRectF(clippedTransformedTargetRect));
2277
2278 QRect clippedSourceRect
2279 = QRectF(sr.x() + clippedTargetRect.x() - r.x(), sr.y() + clippedTargetRect.y() - r.y(),
2280 clippedTargetRect.width(), clippedTargetRect.height()).toRect();
2281
2282 clippedSourceRect = clippedSourceRect.intersected(other: img.rect());
2283
2284 const qsizetype dbpl = d->rasterBuffer->bytesPerLine();
2285 const qsizetype sbpl = img.bytesPerLine();
2286
2287 uchar *dst = d->rasterBuffer->buffer();
2288 uint bpp = img.depth() >> 3;
2289
2290 const uchar *srcBase = img.bits() + clippedSourceRect.y() * sbpl + clippedSourceRect.x() * bpp;
2291 uchar *dstBase = dst + clippedTransformedTargetRect.y() * dbpl + clippedTransformedTargetRect.x() * bpp;
2292
2293 uint cw = clippedSourceRect.width();
2294 uint ch = clippedSourceRect.height();
2295
2296 qMemRotateFunctions[plBpp][rotationType](srcBase, cw, ch, sbpl, dstBase, dbpl);
2297
2298 return;
2299 }
2300 }
2301 }
2302
2303 if (s->matrix.type() > QTransform::TxTranslate || stretch_sr) {
2304
2305 QRectF targetBounds = s->matrix.mapRect(r);
2306 bool exceedsPrecision = r.width() > 0x7fff
2307 || r.height() > 0x7fff
2308 || targetBounds.left() < -0x7fff
2309 || targetBounds.top() < -0x7fff
2310 || targetBounds.right() > 0x7fff
2311 || targetBounds.bottom() > 0x7fff
2312 || targetBounds.width() > 0x7fff
2313 || targetBounds.height() > 0x7fff
2314 || s->matrix.m11() >= 512
2315 || s->matrix.m22() >= 512;
2316 if (!exceedsPrecision && d->canUseFastImageBlending(mode: d->rasterBuffer->compositionMode, image: img)) {
2317 if (s->matrix.type() > QTransform::TxScale) {
2318 SrcOverTransformFunc func = qTransformFunctions[d->rasterBuffer->format][img.format()];
2319 // The fast transform methods doesn't really work on small targets, see QTBUG-93475
2320 // And it can't antialias the edges
2321 if (func && (!clip || clip->hasRectClip) && !s->flags.antialiased && targetBounds.width() >= 16 && targetBounds.height() >= 16) {
2322 func(d->rasterBuffer->buffer(), d->rasterBuffer->bytesPerLine(), img.bits(),
2323 img.bytesPerLine(), r, sr, !clip ? d->deviceRect : clip->clipRect,
2324 s->matrix, s->intOpacity);
2325 return;
2326 }
2327 } else {
2328 // Test for optimized high-dpi case: 2x source on 2x target. (Could be generalized to nX.)
2329 bool sourceRect2x = r.width() * 2 == sr.width() && r.height() * 2 == sr.height();
2330 bool scale2x = (s->matrix.m11() == qreal(2)) && (s->matrix.m22() == qreal(2));
2331 if (s->matrix.type() == QTransform::TxScale && sourceRect2x && scale2x) {
2332 SrcOverBlendFunc func = qBlendFunctions[d->rasterBuffer->format][img.format()];
2333 if (func) {
2334 QPointF pt(r.x() * 2 + s->matrix.dx(), r.y() * 2 + s->matrix.dy());
2335 if (!clip) {
2336 d->drawImage(pt, img, func, clip: d->deviceRect, alpha: s->intOpacity, sr: sr.toRect());
2337 return;
2338 } else if (clip->hasRectClip) {
2339 d->drawImage(pt, img, func, clip: clip->clipRect, alpha: s->intOpacity, sr: sr.toRect());
2340 return;
2341 }
2342 }
2343 }
2344 SrcOverScaleFunc func = qScaleFunctions[d->rasterBuffer->format][img.format()];
2345 if (func && (!clip || clip->hasRectClip)) {
2346 func(d->rasterBuffer->buffer(), d->rasterBuffer->bytesPerLine(),
2347 img.bits(), img.bytesPerLine(), img.height(),
2348 qt_mapRect_non_normalizing(r, t: s->matrix), sr,
2349 !clip ? d->deviceRect : clip->clipRect,
2350 s->intOpacity);
2351 return;
2352 }
2353 }
2354 }
2355
2356 QTransform copy = s->matrix;
2357 copy.translate(dx: r.x(), dy: r.y());
2358 if (stretch_sr)
2359 copy.scale(sx: r.width() / sr.width(), sy: r.height() / sr.height());
2360 copy.translate(dx: -sr.x(), dy: -sr.y());
2361
2362 d->image_filler_xform.clip = clip;
2363 d->image_filler_xform.initTexture(image: &img, alpha: s->intOpacity, QTextureData::Plain, sourceRect: toAlignedRect_positive(rect: sr));
2364 if (!d->image_filler_xform.blend)
2365 return;
2366 d->image_filler_xform.setupMatrix(matrix: copy, bilinear: s->flags.bilinear);
2367
2368 if (!s->flags.antialiased && s->matrix.type() == QTransform::TxScale) {
2369 QRectF rr = s->matrix.mapRect(r);
2370
2371 const int x1 = qRound(d: rr.x());
2372 const int y1 = qRound(d: rr.y());
2373 const int x2 = qRound(d: rr.right());
2374 const int y2 = qRound(d: rr.bottom());
2375
2376 fillRect_normalized(r: QRect(x1, y1, x2-x1, y2-y1), data: &d->image_filler_xform, pe: d);
2377 return;
2378 }
2379
2380#ifdef QT_FAST_SPANS
2381 ensureRasterState();
2382 if (s->flags.tx_noshear || s->matrix.type() == QTransform::TxScale) {
2383 d->initializeRasterizer(data: &d->image_filler_xform);
2384 d->rasterizer->setAntialiased(s->flags.antialiased);
2385
2386 const QRectF &rect = r.normalized();
2387 const QPointF a = s->matrix.map(p: (rect.topLeft() + rect.bottomLeft()) * 0.5f);
2388 const QPointF b = s->matrix.map(p: (rect.topRight() + rect.bottomRight()) * 0.5f);
2389
2390 if (s->flags.tx_noshear)
2391 d->rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a, b, width: rect.height() / rect.width());
2392 else
2393 d->rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a, b, width: qAbs(t: (s->matrix.m22() * rect.height()) / (s->matrix.m11() * rect.width())));
2394 return;
2395 }
2396#endif
2397 QPainterPath path;
2398 path.addRect(rect: r);
2399 QTransform m = s->matrix;
2400 s->matrix = QTransform(m.m11(), m.m12(), m.m13(),
2401 m.m21(), m.m22(), m.m23(),
2402 m.m31(), m.m32(), m.m33());
2403 fillPath(path, fillData: &d->image_filler_xform);
2404 s->matrix = m;
2405 } else {
2406 QPointF pt(r.x() + s->matrix.dx(), r.y() + s->matrix.dy());
2407 if (d->canUseImageBlitting(mode: d->rasterBuffer->compositionMode, image: img, pt, sr)) {
2408 if (!clip) {
2409 d->blitImage(pt, img, clip: d->deviceRect, sr: sr.toRect());
2410 return;
2411 } else if (clip->hasRectClip) {
2412 d->blitImage(pt, img, clip: clip->clipRect, sr: sr.toRect());
2413 return;
2414 }
2415 } else if (d->canUseFastImageBlending(mode: d->rasterBuffer->compositionMode, image: img)) {
2416 SrcOverBlendFunc func = qBlendFunctions[d->rasterBuffer->format][img.format()];
2417 if (func) {
2418 if (!clip) {
2419 d->drawImage(pt, img, func, clip: d->deviceRect, alpha: s->intOpacity, sr: sr.toRect());
2420 return;
2421 } else if (clip->hasRectClip) {
2422 d->drawImage(pt, img, func, clip: clip->clipRect, alpha: s->intOpacity, sr: sr.toRect());
2423 return;
2424 }
2425 }
2426 }
2427
2428 d->image_filler.clip = clip;
2429 d->image_filler.initTexture(image: &img, alpha: s->intOpacity, QTextureData::Plain, sourceRect: toAlignedRect_positive(rect: sr));
2430 if (!d->image_filler.blend)
2431 return;
2432 d->image_filler.dx = -(r.x() + s->matrix.dx()) + sr.x();
2433 d->image_filler.dy = -(r.y() + s->matrix.dy()) + sr.y();
2434
2435 QRectF rr = r;
2436 rr.translate(dx: s->matrix.dx(), dy: s->matrix.dy());
2437
2438 const int x1 = qRound(d: rr.x());
2439 const int y1 = qRound(d: rr.y());
2440 const int x2 = qRound(d: rr.right());
2441 const int y2 = qRound(d: rr.bottom());
2442
2443 fillRect_normalized(r: QRect(x1, y1, x2-x1, y2-y1), data: &d->image_filler, pe: d);

2457 Q_ASSERT(s);
2458

2460
2461 QPlatformPixmap *pd = pixmap.handle();

2467
2468 if (image.depth() == 1)
2469 image = d->rasterBuffer->colorizeBitmap(image, color: s->pen.color());
2470

2483
2484#ifdef QT_FAST_SPANS

2486 if (s->flags.tx_noshear || s->matrix.type() == QTransform::TxScale) {
2487 d->initializeRasterizer(data: &d->image_filler_xform);
2488 d->rasterizer->setAntialiased(s->flags.antialiased);
2489
2490 const QRectF &rect = r.normalized();
2491 const QPointF a = s->matrix.map(p: (rect.topLeft() + rect.bottomLeft()) * 0.5f);
2492 const QPointF b = s->matrix.map(p: (rect.topRight() + rect.bottomRight()) * 0.5f);
2493 if (s->flags.tx_noshear)
2494 d->rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a, b, width: rect.height() / rect.width());
2495 else
2496 d->rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a, b, width: qAbs(t: (s->matrix.m22() * rect.height()) / (s->matrix.m11() * rect.width())));
2497 return;
2498 }
2499#endif
2500 QPainterPath path;
2501 path.addRect(rect: r);
2502 fillPath(path, fillData: &d->image_filler_xform);
2503 } else {
2504 d->image_filler.clip = d->clip();
2505
2506 d->image_filler.initTexture(image: &image, alpha: s->intOpacity, QTextureData::Tiled);
2507 if (!d->image_filler.blend)
2508 return;
2509 d->image_filler.dx = -(r.x() + s->matrix.dx()) + sr.x();
2510 d->image_filler.dy = -(r.y() + s->matrix.dy()) + sr.y();
2511

2513 rr.translate(dx: s->matrix.dx(), dy: s->matrix.dy());

2537void QRasterPaintEngine::alphaPenBlt(const void* src, int bpl, int depth, int rx,int ry,int w,int h, bool useGammaCorrection)

2542 if (!s->penData.blend)
2543 return;
2544
2545 QRasterBuffer *rb = d->rasterBuffer.data();
2546 if (rb->colorSpace.transferFunction() == QColorSpace::TransferFunction::Linear)
2547 useGammaCorrection = false;
2548
2549 const QRect rect(rx, ry, w, h);
2550 const QClipData *clip = d->clip();
2551 bool unclipped = false;
2552 if (clip) {
2553 // inlined QRect::intersects
2554 const bool intersects = qMax(a: clip->xmin, b: rect.left()) <= qMin(a: clip->xmax - 1, b: rect.right())
2555 && qMax(a: clip->ymin, b: rect.top()) <= qMin(a: clip->ymax - 1, b: rect.bottom());
2556
2557 if (clip->hasRectClip) {
2558 unclipped = rx > clip->xmin
2559 && rx + w < clip->xmax
2560 && ry > clip->ymin
2561 && ry + h < clip->ymax;
2562 }
2563
2564 if (!intersects)
2565 return;
2566 } else {
2567 // inlined QRect::intersects
2568 const bool intersects = qMax(a: 0, b: rect.left()) <= qMin(a: rb->width() - 1, b: rect.right())
2569 && qMax(a: 0, b: rect.top()) <= qMin(a: rb->height() - 1, b: rect.bottom());
2570 if (!intersects)
2571 return;
2572
2573 // inlined QRect::contains
2574 const bool contains = rect.left() >= 0 && rect.right() < rb->width()
2575 && rect.top() >= 0 && rect.bottom() < rb->height();
2576
2577 unclipped = contains && d->isUnclipped_normalized(rect);
2578 }
2579
2580 ProcessSpans blend = unclipped ? s->penData.unclipped_blend : s->penData.blend;
2581 const uchar * scanline = static_cast<const uchar *>(src);
2582
2583 if (s->flags.fast_text) {
2584 if (unclipped) {
2585 if (depth == 1) {
2586 if (s->penData.bitmapBlit) {
2587 s->penData.bitmapBlit(rb, rx, ry, s->penData.solidColor.rgba64(),
2588 scanline, w, h, bpl);
2589 return;
2590 }
2591 } else if (depth == 8) {
2592 if (s->penData.alphamapBlit) {
2593 s->penData.alphamapBlit(rb, rx, ry, s->penData.solidColor.rgba64(),
2594 scanline, w, h, bpl, nullptr, useGammaCorrection);
2595 return;
2596 }
2597 } else if (depth == 32) {
2598 // (A)RGB Alpha mask where the alpha component is not used.
2599 if (s->penData.alphaRGBBlit) {
2600 s->penData.alphaRGBBlit(rb, rx, ry, s->penData.solidColor.rgba64(),
2601 (const uint *) scanline, w, h, bpl / 4, nullptr, useGammaCorrection);
2602 return;
2603 }
2604 }
2605 } else if ((depth == 8 && s->penData.alphamapBlit) || (depth == 32 && s->penData.alphaRGBBlit)) {
2606 // (A)RGB Alpha mask where the alpha component is not used.
2607 if (!clip) {
2608 int nx = qMax(a: 0, b: rx);
2609 int ny = qMax(a: 0, b: ry);
2610
2611 // Move scanline pointer to compensate for moved x and y
2612 int xdiff = nx - rx;
2613 int ydiff = ny - ry;
2614 scanline += ydiff * bpl;
2615 scanline += xdiff * (depth == 32 ? 4 : 1);
2616
2617 w -= xdiff;
2618 h -= ydiff;
2619
2620 if (nx + w > d->rasterBuffer->width())
2621 w = d->rasterBuffer->width() - nx;
2622 if (ny + h > d->rasterBuffer->height())
2623 h = d->rasterBuffer->height() - ny;
2624
2625 rx = nx;
2626 ry = ny;
2627 }
2628 if (depth == 8)
2629 s->penData.alphamapBlit(rb, rx, ry, s->penData.solidColor.rgba64(),
2630 scanline, w, h, bpl, clip, useGammaCorrection);
2631 else if (depth == 32)
2632 s->penData.alphaRGBBlit(rb, rx, ry, s->penData.solidColor.rgba64(),
2633 (const uint *) scanline, w, h, bpl / 4, clip, useGammaCorrection);
2634 return;
2635 }
2636 }
2637
2638 int x0 = 0;
2639 if (rx < 0) {
2640 x0 = -rx;
2641 w -= x0;
2642 }
2643
2644 int y0 = 0;
2645 if (ry < 0) {
2646 y0 = -ry;
2647 scanline += bpl * y0;
2648 h -= y0;
2649 }
2650
2651 w = qMin(a: w, b: rb->width() - qMax(a: 0, b: rx));
2652 h = qMin(a: h, b: rb->height() - qMax(a: 0, b: ry));
2653
2654 if (w <= 0 || h <= 0)
2655 return;
2656
2657 const int NSPANS = 512;
2658 QT_FT_Span spans[NSPANS];
2659 int current = 0;
2660
2661 const int x1 = x0 + w;
2662 const int y1 = y0 + h;
2663
2664 if (depth == 1) {
2665 for (int y = y0; y < y1; ++y) {
2666 for (int x = x0; x < x1; ) {
2667 if (!monoVal(s: scanline, x)) {
2668 ++x;
2669 continue;
2670 }
2671
2672 if (current == NSPANS) {
2673 blend(current, spans, &s->penData);
2674 current = 0;
2675 }
2676 spans[current].x = x + rx;
2677 spans[current].y = y + ry;
2678 spans[current].coverage = 255;
2679 int len = 1;
2680 ++x;
2681 // extend span until we find a different one.
2682 while (x < x1 && monoVal(s: scanline, x)) {
2683 ++x;
2684 ++len;
2685 }
2686 spans[current].len = len;
2687 ++current;
2688 }
2689 scanline += bpl;
2690 }
2691 } else if (depth == 8) {
2692 for (int y = y0; y < y1; ++y) {
2693 for (int x = x0; x < x1; ) {
2694 // Skip those with 0 coverage
2695 if (scanline[x] == 0) {
2696 ++x;
2697 continue;
2698 }
2699
2700 if (current == NSPANS) {
2701 blend(current, spans, &s->penData);
2702 current = 0;
2703 }
2704 int coverage = scanline[x];
2705 spans[current].x = x + rx;
2706 spans[current].y = y + ry;
2707 spans[current].coverage = coverage;
2708 int len = 1;
2709 ++x;
2710
2711 // extend span until we find a different one.
2712 while (x < x1 && scanline[x] == coverage) {
2713 ++x;
2714 ++len;
2715 }
2716 spans[current].len = len;
2717 ++current;
2718 }
2719 scanline += bpl;
2720 }
2721 } else { // 32-bit alpha...
2722 const uint *sl = (const uint *) scanline;
2723 for (int y = y0; y < y1; ++y) {
2724 for (int x = x0; x < x1; ) {
2725 // Skip those with 0 coverage
2726 if ((sl[x] & 0x00ffffff) == 0) {
2727 ++x;
2728 continue;
2729 }
2730
2731 if (current == NSPANS) {
2732 blend(current, spans, &s->penData);
2733 current = 0;
2734 }
2735 uint rgbCoverage = sl[x];
2736 int coverage = qGreen(rgb: rgbCoverage);
2737 spans[current].x = x + rx;
2738 spans[current].y = y + ry;
2739 spans[current].coverage = coverage;
2740 int len = 1;
2741 ++x;
2742
2743 // extend span until we find a different one.
2744 while (x < x1 && sl[x] == rgbCoverage) {
2745 ++x;
2746 ++len;
2747 }
2748 spans[current].len = len;
2749 ++current;
2750 }
2751 sl += bpl / sizeof(uint);
2752 }
2753 }
2754// qDebug() << "alphaPenBlt: num spans=" << current
2755// << "span:" << spans->x << spans->y << spans->len << spans->coverage;
2756 // Call span func for current set of spans.
2757 if (current != 0)
2758 blend(current, spans, &s->penData);
2759}

2761/*!
2762 \internal
2763*/
2764bool QRasterPaintEngine::drawCachedGlyphs(int numGlyphs, const glyph_t *glyphs,
2765 const QFixedPoint *positions, QFontEngine *fontEngine)
2766{
2767 Q_D(QRasterPaintEngine);
2768 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = state();
2769
2770 bool verticalSubPixelPositions = fontEngine->supportsVerticalSubPixelPositions()
2771 && (s->renderHints & QPainter::VerticalSubpixelPositioning) != 0;
2772
2773 if (fontEngine->hasInternalCaching()) {
2774 QFontEngine::GlyphFormat neededFormat =
2775 painter()->device()->devType() == QInternal::Widget
2776 ? QFontEngine::Format_None
2777 : QFontEngine::Format_A8;
2778
2779 if (d_func()->mono_surface) // alphaPenBlt can handle mono, too
2780 neededFormat = QFontEngine::Format_Mono;
2781
2782 for (int i = 0; i < numGlyphs; i++) {
2783 QFixedPoint spp = fontEngine->subPixelPositionFor(position: positions[i]);
2784 if (!verticalSubPixelPositions)
2785 spp.y = 0;
2786
2787 const QFontEngine::Glyph *alphaMap = fontEngine->glyphData(glyph: glyphs[i], subPixelPosition: spp, neededFormat, t: s->matrix);
2788 if (!alphaMap)
2789 continue;
2790
2791 int depth;
2792 int bytesPerLine;
2793 switch (alphaMap->format) {
2794 case QFontEngine::Format_Mono:
2795 depth = 1;
2796 bytesPerLine = ((alphaMap->width + 31) & ~31) >> 3;
2797 break;
2798 case QFontEngine::Format_A8:
2799 depth = 8;
2800 bytesPerLine = (alphaMap->width + 3) & ~3;
2801 break;
2802 case QFontEngine::Format_A32:
2803 depth = 32;
2804 bytesPerLine = alphaMap->width * 4;
2805 break;
2806 default:
2807 Q_UNREACHABLE();
2808 };
2809
2810 QFixed y = verticalSubPixelPositions
2811 ? qFloor(f: positions[i].y)
2812 : qRound(f: positions[i].y);
2813
2814 alphaPenBlt(src: alphaMap->data, bpl: bytesPerLine, depth,
2815 rx: qFloor(f: positions[i].x) + alphaMap->x,
2816 ry: qFloor(f: y) - alphaMap->y,
2817 w: alphaMap->width, h: alphaMap->height,
2818 useGammaCorrection: fontEngine->expectsGammaCorrectedBlending());
2819 }
2820
2821 } else {
2822 QFontEngine::GlyphFormat glyphFormat = fontEngine->glyphFormat != QFontEngine::Format_None ? fontEngine->glyphFormat : d->glyphCacheFormat;
2823
2824 QImageTextureGlyphCache *cache =
2825 static_cast<QImageTextureGlyphCache *>(fontEngine->glyphCache(key: nullptr, format: glyphFormat, transform: s->matrix, color: s->penData.solidColor));
2826 if (!cache) {
2827 cache = new QImageTextureGlyphCache(glyphFormat, s->matrix, s->penData.solidColor);
2828 fontEngine->setGlyphCache(key: nullptr, data: cache);
2829 }
2830
2831 cache->populate(fontEngine, numGlyphs, glyphs, positions, renderHints: s->renderHints);
2832 cache->fillInPendingGlyphs();
2833
2834 const QImage &image = cache->image();
2835 qsizetype bpl = image.bytesPerLine();
2836
2837 int depth = image.depth();
2838 int rightShift = 0;
2839 int leftShift = 0;
2840 if (depth == 32)
2841 leftShift = 2; // multiply by 4
2842 else if (depth == 1)
2843 rightShift = 3; // divide by 8
2844
2845 int margin = fontEngine->glyphMargin(format: glyphFormat);
2846 const uchar *bits = image.bits();
2847 for (int i=0; i<numGlyphs; ++i) {
2848 QFixedPoint subPixelPosition = fontEngine->subPixelPositionFor(position: positions[i]);
2849 if (!verticalSubPixelPositions)
2850 subPixelPosition.y = 0;
2851
2852 QTextureGlyphCache::GlyphAndSubPixelPosition glyph(glyphs[i], subPixelPosition);
2853 const QTextureGlyphCache::Coord &c = cache->coords[glyph];
2854 if (c.isNull())
2855 continue;
2856
2857 int x = qFloor(f: positions[i].x) + c.baseLineX - margin;
2858 int y = (verticalSubPixelPositions
2859 ? qFloor(f: positions[i].y)
2860 : qRound(f: positions[i].y));
2861 y -= c.baseLineY + margin;
2862
2863 // printf("drawing [%d %d %d %d] baseline [%d %d], glyph: %d, to: %d %d, pos: %d %d\n",
2864 // c.x, c.y,
2865 // c.w, c.h,
2866 // c.baseLineX, c.baseLineY,
2867 // glyphs[i],
2868 // x, y,
2869 // positions[i].x.toInt(), positions[i].y.toInt());
2870
2871 const uchar *glyphBits = bits + ((c.x << leftShift) >> rightShift) + c.y * bpl;
2872
2873 if (glyphFormat == QFontEngine::Format_ARGB) {
2874 // The current state transform has already been applied to the positions,
2875 // so we prevent drawImage() from re-applying the transform by clearing
2876 // the state for the duration of the call.
2877 QTransform originalTransform = s->matrix;
2878 s->matrix = QTransform();
2879 drawImage(p: QPoint(x, y), img: QImage(glyphBits, c.w, c.h, bpl, image.format()));
2880 s->matrix = originalTransform;
2881 } else {
2882 alphaPenBlt(src: glyphBits, bpl, depth, rx: x, ry: y, w: c.w, h: c.h, useGammaCorrection: fontEngine->expectsGammaCorrectedBlending());
2883 }
2884 }
2885 }
2886 return true;
2887}

2892 * state of the paint engine.

2894bool QRasterPaintEnginePrivate::isUnclipped_normalized(const QRect &r) const
2895{
2896 const QClipData *cl = clip();
2897 if (!cl) {
2898 // inline contains() for performance (we know the rects are normalized)
2899 const QRect &r1 = deviceRect;
2900 return (r.left() >= r1.left() && r.right() <= r1.right()
2901 && r.top() >= r1.top() && r.bottom() <= r1.bottom());
2902 }
2903
2904
2905 if (cl->hasRectClip) {
2906 // currently all painting functions clips to deviceRect internally
2907 if (cl->clipRect == deviceRect)
2908 return true;
2909
2910 // inline contains() for performance (we know the rects are normalized)
2911 const QRect &r1 = cl->clipRect;
2912 return (r.left() >= r1.left() && r.right() <= r1.right()
2913 && r.top() >= r1.top() && r.bottom() <= r1.bottom());
2914 } else {
2915 return qt_region_strictContains(region: cl->clipRegion, rect: r);
2916 }

2919bool QRasterPaintEnginePrivate::isUnclipped(const QRect &rect,
2920 int penWidth) const
2921{
2922 Q_Q(const QRasterPaintEngine);
2923 const QRasterPaintEngineState *s = q->state();
2924 const QClipData *cl = clip();
2925 QRect r = rect.normalized();
2926 if (!cl) {
2927 // inline contains() for performance (we know the rects are normalized)
2928 const QRect &r1 = deviceRect;
2929 return (r.left() >= r1.left() && r.right() <= r1.right()
2930 && r.top() >= r1.top() && r.bottom() <= r1.bottom());
2931 }
2932
2933
2934 // currently all painting functions that call this function clip to deviceRect internally
2935 if (cl->hasRectClip && cl->clipRect == deviceRect)
2936 return true;
2937
2938 if (s->flags.antialiased)
2939 ++penWidth;
2940
2941 if (penWidth > 0) {
2942 r.setX(r.x() - penWidth);
2943 r.setY(r.y() - penWidth);
2944 r.setWidth(r.width() + 2 * penWidth);
2945 r.setHeight(r.height() + 2 * penWidth);
2946 }
2947
2948 if (cl->hasRectClip) {
2949 // inline contains() for performance (we know the rects are normalized)
2950 const QRect &r1 = cl->clipRect;
2951 return (r.left() >= r1.left() && r.right() <= r1.right()
2952 && r.top() >= r1.top() && r.bottom() <= r1.bottom());
2953 } else {
2954 return qt_region_strictContains(region: cl->clipRegion, rect: r);
2955 }
2956}

2963 || norm.right() > INT_MAX || norm.bottom() > INT_MAX

3199void QRasterPaintEnginePrivate::rasterizeLine_dashed(QLineF line,
3200 qreal width,
3201 int *dashIndex,
3202 qreal *dashOffset,
3203 bool *inDash)
3204{
3205 Q_Q(QRasterPaintEngine);
3206 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = q->state();
3207
3208 const QPen &pen = s->lastPen;
3209 const bool squareCap = (pen.capStyle() == Qt::SquareCap);
3210 const QList<qreal> pattern = pen.dashPattern();
3211
3212 qreal patternLength = 0;
3213 for (int i = 0; i < pattern.size(); ++i)
3214 patternLength += pattern.at(i);
3215
3216 if (patternLength <= 0)
3217 return;
3218
3219 qreal length = line.length();
3220 Q_ASSERT(length > 0);
3221 if (length / (patternLength * width) > QDashStroker::repetitionLimit()) {
3222 rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a: line.p1(), b: line.p2(), width: width / length, squareCap);
3223 return;
3224 }
3225
3226 while (length > 0) {
3227 const bool rasterize = *inDash;
3228 qreal dash = (pattern.at(i: *dashIndex) - *dashOffset) * width;
3229 QLineF l = line;
3230
3231 if (dash >= length) {
3232 dash = line.length(); // Avoid accumulated precision error in 'length'
3233 *dashOffset += dash / width;
3234 length = 0;
3235 } else {
3236 *dashOffset = 0;
3237 *inDash = !(*inDash);
3238 if (++*dashIndex >= pattern.size())
3239 *dashIndex = 0;
3240 length -= dash;
3241 l.setLength(dash);
3242 line.setP1(l.p2());
3243 }
3244
3245 if (rasterize && dash > 0)
3246 rasterizer->rasterizeLine(a: l.p1(), b: l.p2(), width: width / dash, squareCap);
3247 }
3248}

3349/*!
3350 Returns whether glyph caching is supported by the font engine
3351 \a fontEngine with the given transform \a m applied.
3352*/
3353bool QRasterPaintEngine::shouldDrawCachedGlyphs(QFontEngine *fontEngine, const QTransform &m) const
3354{
3355 // The raster engine does not support projected cached glyph drawing
3356 if (m.type() >= QTransform::TxProject)
3357 return false;
3358
3359 // The font engine might not support filling the glyph cache
3360 // with the given transform applied, in which case we need to
3361 // fall back to the QPainterPath code-path. This does not apply
3362 // for engines with internal caching, as we don't use the engine
3363 // to fill up our cache in that case.
3364 if (!fontEngine->hasInternalCaching() && !fontEngine->supportsTransformation(transform: m))
3365 return false;
3366
3367 return QPaintEngineEx::shouldDrawCachedGlyphs(fontEngine, m);

3378void QRasterPaintEngine::drawBitmap(const QPointF &pos, const QImage &image, QSpanData *fg)
3379{

3381 if (!fg->blend)
3382 return;

3385 Q_ASSERT(image.depth() == 1);
3386
3387 const int spanCount = 512;
3388 QT_FT_Span spans[spanCount];
3389 int n = 0;

3391 // Boundaries
3392 int w = image.width();
3393 int h = image.height();
3394 int ymax = qMin(a: qRound(d: pos.y() + h), b: d->rasterBuffer->height());
3395 int ymin = qMax(a: qRound(d: pos.y()), b: 0);
3396 int xmax = qMin(a: qRound(d: pos.x() + w), b: d->rasterBuffer->width());

3399 int x_offset = xmin - qRound(d: pos.x());
3400
3401 QImage::Format format = image.format();
3402 for (int y = ymin; y < ymax; ++y) {
3403 const uchar *src = image.scanLine(y - qRound(d: pos.y()));
3404 if (format == QImage::Format_MonoLSB) {
3405 for (int x = 0; x < xmax - xmin; ++x) {
3406 int src_x = x + x_offset;
3407 uchar pixel = src[src_x >> 3];
3408 if (!pixel) {
3409 x += 7 - (src_x%8);
3410 continue;
3411 }
3412 if (pixel & (0x1 << (src_x & 7))) {
3413 spans[n].x = xmin + x;
3414 spans[n].y = y;
3415 spans[n].coverage = 255;
3416 int len = 1;
3417 while (src_x+1 < w && src[(src_x+1) >> 3] & (0x1 << ((src_x+1) & 7))) {
3418 ++src_x;
3419 ++len;
3420 }
3421 spans[n].len = ((len + spans[n].x) > xmax) ? (xmax - spans[n].x) : len;
3422 x += len;
3423 ++n;
3424 if (n == spanCount) {
3425 fg->blend(n, spans, fg);
3426 n = 0;
3427 }
3428 }
3429 }
3430 } else {
3431 for (int x = 0; x < xmax - xmin; ++x) {
3432 int src_x = x + x_offset;
3433 uchar pixel = src[src_x >> 3];
3434 if (!pixel) {
3435 x += 7 - (src_x%8);
3436 continue;
3437 }
3438 if (pixel & (0x80 >> (x & 7))) {
3439 spans[n].x = xmin + x;
3440 spans[n].y = y;
3441 spans[n].coverage = 255;
3442 int len = 1;
3443 while (src_x+1 < w && src[(src_x+1) >> 3] & (0x80 >> ((src_x+1) & 7))) {
3444 ++src_x;
3445 ++len;
3446 }
3447 spans[n].len = ((len + spans[n].x) > xmax) ? (xmax - spans[n].x) : len;
3448 x += len;
3449 ++n;
3450 if (n == spanCount) {
3451 fg->blend(n, spans, fg);
3452 n = 0;
3453 }
3454 }
3455 }
3456 }
3457 }
3458 if (n) {
3459 fg->blend(n, spans, fg);
3460 n = 0;

3560{
3561 return (uchar *)(((quintptr)address + alignmentMask) & ~alignmentMask);
3562}
3563
3564void QRasterPaintEnginePrivate::rasterize(QT_FT_Outline *outline,
3565 ProcessSpans callback,
3566 void *userData, QRasterBuffer *)
3567{
3568 if (!callback || !outline)
3569 return;
3570
3571 Q_Q(QRasterPaintEngine);
3572 QRasterPaintEngineState *s = q->state();
3573
3574 if (!s->flags.antialiased) {
3575 rasterizer->setAntialiased(s->flags.antialiased);
3576 rasterizer->setClipRect(deviceRect);
3577 rasterizer->initialize(blend: callback, data: userData);
3578
3579 const Qt::FillRule fillRule = outline->flags == QT_FT_OUTLINE_NONE
3580 ? Qt::WindingFill
3581 : Qt::OddEvenFill;
3582
3583 rasterizer->rasterize(outline, fillRule);
3584 return;
3585 }
3586
3587 // Initial size for raster pool is MINIMUM_POOL_SIZE so as to
3588 // minimize memory reallocations. However if initial size for
3589 // raster pool is changed for lower value, reallocations will
3590 // occur normally.
3591 int rasterPoolSize = MINIMUM_POOL_SIZE;
3592 uchar rasterPoolOnStack[MINIMUM_POOL_SIZE + 0xf];
3593 uchar *rasterPoolBase = alignAddress(address: rasterPoolOnStack, alignmentMask: 0xf);
3594 uchar *rasterPoolOnHeap = nullptr;
3595
3596 qt_ft_grays_raster.raster_reset(*grayRaster.data(), rasterPoolBase, rasterPoolSize);
3597
3598 void *data = userData;
3599
3600 QT_FT_BBox clip_box = { .xMin: deviceRect.x(),
3601 .yMin: deviceRect.y(),
3602 .xMax: deviceRect.x() + deviceRect.width(),
3603 .yMax: deviceRect.y() + deviceRect.height() };
3604
3605 QT_FT_Raster_Params rasterParams;
3606 rasterParams.target = nullptr;
3607 rasterParams.source = outline;
3608 rasterParams.flags = QT_FT_RASTER_FLAG_CLIP;
3609 rasterParams.gray_spans = nullptr;
3610 rasterParams.black_spans = nullptr;
3611 rasterParams.bit_test = nullptr;
3612 rasterParams.bit_set = nullptr;
3613 rasterParams.user = data;
3614 rasterParams.clip_box = clip_box;
3615
3616 bool done = false;
3617 int error;
3618
3619 int rendered_spans = 0;
3620
3621 while (!done) {
3622
3623 rasterParams.flags |= (QT_FT_RASTER_FLAG_AA | QT_FT_RASTER_FLAG_DIRECT);
3624 rasterParams.gray_spans = callback;
3625 rasterParams.skip_spans = rendered_spans;
3626 error = qt_ft_grays_raster.raster_render(*grayRaster.data(), &rasterParams);
3627
3628 // Out of memory, reallocate some more and try again...
3629 if (error == -6) { // ErrRaster_OutOfMemory from qgrayraster.c
3630 rasterPoolSize *= 2;
3631 if (rasterPoolSize > 1024 * 1024) {
3632 qWarning(msg: "QPainter: Rasterization of primitive failed");
3633 break;
3634 }
3635
3636 rendered_spans += q_gray_rendered_spans(raster: *grayRaster.data());
3637
3638 free(ptr: rasterPoolOnHeap);
3639 rasterPoolOnHeap = (uchar *)malloc(size: rasterPoolSize + 0xf);
3640
3641 Q_CHECK_PTR(rasterPoolOnHeap); // note: we just freed the old rasterPoolBase. I hope it's not fatal.
3642
3643 rasterPoolBase = alignAddress(address: rasterPoolOnHeap, alignmentMask: 0xf);
3644
3645 qt_ft_grays_raster.raster_done(*grayRaster.data());
3646 qt_ft_grays_raster.raster_new(grayRaster.data());
3647 qt_ft_grays_raster.raster_reset(*grayRaster.data(), rasterPoolBase, rasterPoolSize);
3648 } else {
3649 done = true;
3650 }
3651 }
3652
3653 free(ptr: rasterPoolOnHeap);
3654}

3687
3688bool QRasterPaintEnginePrivate::canUseImageBlitting(QPainter::CompositionMode mode, const QImage &image, const QPointF &pt, const QRectF &sr) const
3689{
3690 Q_Q(const QRasterPaintEngine);
3691
3692 if (!(mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_Source
3693 || (mode == QPainter::CompositionMode_SourceOver
3694 && !image.hasAlphaChannel())))
3695 return false;
3696
3697 const QRasterPaintEngineState *s = q->state();
3698 Q_ASSERT(s->matrix.type() <= QTransform::TxTranslate || s->matrix.type() == QTransform::TxRotate);
3699
3700 if (s->intOpacity != 256
3701 || image.depth() < 8
3702 || ((s->renderHints & (QPainter::SmoothPixmapTransform | QPainter::Antialiasing))
3703 && (!isPixelAligned(pt) || !isPixelAligned(rect: sr))))
3704 return false;
3705
3706 QImage::Format dFormat = rasterBuffer->format;
3707 QImage::Format sFormat = image.format();
3708 // Formats must match or source format must be a subset of destination format
3709 if (dFormat != sFormat && image.pixelFormat().alphaUsage() == QPixelFormat::IgnoresAlpha) {
3710 if ((sFormat == QImage::Format_RGB32 && dFormat == QImage::Format_ARGB32)
3711 || (sFormat == QImage::Format_RGBX8888 && dFormat == QImage::Format_RGBA8888)
3712 || (sFormat == QImage::Format_RGBX64 && dFormat == QImage::Format_RGBA64))
3713 sFormat = dFormat;
3714 else
3715 sFormat = qt_maybeAlphaVersionWithSameDepth(format: sFormat); // this returns premul formats
3716 }
3717 return (dFormat == sFormat);
3718}
